  "texts": [
    "This approach benefits few-shot learning, especially when dealing with outliers.",
    "In the context of metric learning, Zhang et al. (2021a) argue that sample-to-sample learning is computationally expensive, while sample-to-prototype learning is less accurate.",
    "They propose a hybrid strategy based on grouplets.",
    "Each grouplet is a random subset of samples and the set of grouplets is matched with prototypes through a differentiable optimal transport.",
    "Akin to Ermolov et al. (2022), they show that using hyperbolic embedding spaces improved metric learning on fine-grained datasets."
